        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 6:49PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 647 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Berne, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail. Brief funnel
clouds are possible.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Portland, Berne, Geneva, Monroe, Westchester, Bryant, Vera Cruz,
Trinity, Ceylon, Reiffsburg, Linn Grove, Domestic, and New Corydon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Weak, brief funnel clouds are possible. This type of funnel cloud is
harmless, but on rare occasions they can briefly touch down,
producing wind gusts over 50 mph. If a funnel cloud is spotted move
indoors and report your sighting to the National Weather Service.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
